      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) represents a mechanically sound example of the legendary S54-powered platform. The 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six features individual throttle bodies and high-pressure VANOS variable valve timing, providing a visceral 8,000 RPM redline and sharp throttle response. Power is delivered through a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a variable M differential lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution across the rear axle. The chassis has been enhanced with essential subframe reinforcement to address known E46-generation fatigue points, and the suspension retains its factory-intended kinematics with crisp turn-in and high lateral stability. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the drivetrain and cooling system have been meticulously maintained, preserving the high-performance envelope of this motorsport-derived icon.",
